{"id":"1906.00918","submitter":"Oscar Bandtlow","authors":"Oscar F. Bandtlow and St\\'ephanie Nivoche","title":"New solution of a problem of Kolmogorov on width asymptotics in\n  holomorphic function spaces","comments":"34 pages; strengthened result: compact $K$ now only assumed to be\n  non-pluripolar","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CA math.CV math.FA math.SP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Given a domain $D$ in $\\mathbb{C}^n$ and $K$ a compact subset of $D$, the set\n$\\mathcal{A}_K^D$ of all restrictions of functions holomorphic on $D$ the\nmodulus of which is bounded by $1$ is a compact subset of the Banach space\n$C(K)$ of continuous functions on $K$. The sequence\n$(d_m(\\mathcal{A}_K^D))_{m\\in \\mathbb{N}}$ of Kolmogorov $m$-widths of\n$\\mathcal{A}_K^D$ provides a measure of the degree of compactness of the set\n$\\mathcal{A}_K^D$ in $C(K)$ and the study of its asymptotics has a long\nhistory, essentially going back to Kolmogorov's work on $\\epsilon$-entropy of\ncompact sets in the 1950s. In the 1980s Zakharyuta showed that for suitable $D$\nand $K$ the asymptotics \\begin{equation*}\n  \\lim_{m\\to \\infty}\\frac{- \\log d_m(\\mathcal{A}_K^D)}{m^{1/n}} =\n  2\\pi \\left ( \\frac{n!}{C(K,D)}\\right ) ^{1/n}\\,, \\end{equation*} where\n$C(K,D)$ is the Bedford-Taylor relative capacity of $K$ in $D$ is implied by a\nconjecture, now known as Zakharyuta's Conjecture, concerning the\napproximability of the regularised relative extremal function of $K$ and $D$ by\ncertain pluricomplex Green functions. Zakharyuta's Conjecture was proved by\nNivoche in 2004 thus settling the asymptotics above at the same time.\n  We shall give a new proof of the asymptotics above for $D$ strictly\nhyperconvex and $K$ non-pluripolar which does not rely on Zakharyuta's\nConjecture. Instead we proceed more directly by a two-pronged approach\nestablishing sharp upper and lower bounds for the Kolmogorov widths. The lower\nbounds follow from concentration results of independent interest for the\neigenvalues of a certain family of Toeplitz operators, while the upper bounds\nfollow from an application of the Bergman-Weil formula together with an\nexhaustion procedure by special holomorphic polyhedra.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Jun 2019 16:40:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 19 May 2020 14:04:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
