 basis for managing the more interesting Prony problem for exponential\nsums with equal weights $H_n(z;\\exp)$, i.e. when $h(z)=\\exp(z)$. We show that\nit is uniquely solvable and surprisingly $\\mu$ and $\\lambda_k$ can be\nefficiently estimated. This is in sharp contrast to the case of well-known\nexponential sums $\\mathcal{H}_n(z;\\exp)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Jun 2019 10:43:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Jul 2019 12:18:03 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 3 Jan 2020 12:02:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-06"}
